  "text": "To establish that our results are not plagued with publication bias, we follow Stanley (2008) and [CITATION_1] and use the Funnel Assymetry Test (FAT) to test for the presence of publication bias. FAT estimates equation (1), assuming that all a k are zero, i.e. no heterogeneity effect and tests the null hypothesis H 0 : β 0 =0. A non-rejection of the null is consistent with the assumption of absence of publication bias. A non-zero constant term on the other hand implies upward or downward bias (depending on whether β 0 is positive or negative respectively) on the effects estimated in the literature. 13 The results of the FAT test are presented in Table 3. [Insert Table 3 , here]",
